---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Allianz Care in Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-allianz', text: 'Why Allianz for Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Who It\'s Best For', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Colombia', href: '/countries/colombia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Allianz vs Cigna', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 35)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Essential', coverage: 'Inpatient only', price: '$100-130/mo' },
  { plan: 'Classic', coverage: 'Inpatient + basic outpatient', price: '$130-180/mo' },
  { plan: 'Premium', coverage: 'Comprehensive', price: '$180-220/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz Care Health Insurance in Colombia"
  description="Guide to Allianz Care international health insurance for expats in Colombia. Affordable comprehensive coverage for Medellín, Bogotá, and beyond."
  headline="Allianz Care in Colombia"
  subheadline="Strong value proposition for Colombia expats. Comprehensive coverage at competitive prices from a trusted global insurer."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/colombia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Allianz Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Allianz Care in Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers a compelling balance of comprehensive coverage and competitive pricing that works well for Colombia's expat community. As one of the world's largest insurers, Allianz brings financial stability and a global network to the table.
  </p>
  <p>
    For expats looking for solid international coverage without premium pricing, Allianz represents strong value—particularly in Colombia where healthcare costs are already reasonable.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$130-220</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 35)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Good Value</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Competitive pricing</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Global Network</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Worldwide coverage</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Allianz Colombia Quote"
    description="Quality coverage at competitive prices for Colombia expats."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-allianz">Why Allianz for Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care works well for Colombia expats for several reasons:
  </p>

  <h3>Price-to-Coverage Ratio</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz typically offers 10-20% lower premiums than Cigna or BUPA for comparable coverage levels. In Colombia, where healthcare costs are already low, this makes Allianz an attractive option.
  </p>

  <h3>Hospital Access</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz's network includes Colombia's major hospitals:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Fundación Santa Fe (Bogotá):</strong> In-network, direct billing</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital Pablo Tobón Uribe (Medellín):</strong> Network facility</li>
    <li><strong>Major private hospitals:</strong> Throughout Colombia's cities</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Flexible Plans</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Multiple coverage tiers to match your budget</li>
    <li>Optional add-ons for dental, vision, wellness</li>
    <li>Adjustable deductibles for cost control</li>
    <li>Area of coverage options (regional vs worldwide)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Digital Experience</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>User-friendly member portal</li>
    <li>Mobile app for claims and ID cards</li>
    <li>Online pre-authorization for procedures</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 35-year-old. Actual premiums depend on age, health history, selected coverage, and deductible.
  </p>

  <h3>Cost Factors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age:</strong> Premiums increase with age</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage area:</strong> Americas-only is cheaper than worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Deductible:</strong> Higher deductibles reduce premiums significantly</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> Including US increases costs 30-40%</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, ICU, cancer treatment</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists, diagnostics (Classic+)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation and repatriation</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Coverage included (with limits)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: Moratorium or underwriting options</li>
    <li>Maternity: Waiting period applies, optional on some plans</li>
    <li>Dental/vision: Optional add-on</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Who It's Best For</h2>

  <h3>Value-Conscious Expats</h3>
  <p>
    If you want comprehensive international coverage but don't want to pay premium prices, Allianz offers excellent value. The savings compared to Cigna or BUPA can add up significantly over time.
  </p>

  <h3>Long-term Residents</h3>
  <p>
    For expats planning to stay in Colombia for several years, Allianz's competitive pricing makes it sustainable long-term without sacrificing quality coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Digital Nomads</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz meets Colombia's visa requirements and provides worldwide coverage for frequent travelers. The mobile app makes managing your insurance on the go straightforward.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Visa Compliance</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      Allianz Care meets Colombia's digital nomad visa insurance requirements. Your policy documents can serve as proof of coverage for visa applications.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Allianz Plans for Colombia"
    description="Find the right coverage at the right price."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details are estimates based on typical scenarios. Get a personalized quote for accurate pricing based on your age, health, and coverage needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
